description: Impulse decides to help out the target of the local bullies. Using his power, he causes the boy to gain admiration, for the bullies now think their former target is capable of great athletic feats. But soon Impulse comes to realize the kid had not made new friends, only thrill-seekers by proxy and he works to solve that situation as well.
name: Water Rat

description: En route with Ragged Robin to rescue Dane, the young Invisible named Boy recounts her dramatic past as a New York City cop, where she had to make hard decisions regarding her two brothers -- and learned the workings of the city's secret government.
name: How I Became Invisible

description: Ariana bleached her hair because she saw Tim eye-balling a blonde (Stephanie Brown). She instantly became more popular at school, putting Tim in a bad mood. He went out as Robin to get his mind off it. He was captured by Maxie Zeus' gang who demanded to meet "the Oracle."
name: Hit and Myths

description: Mysterious accidents continue to occur all across the city and the Golden Age Sandman heads out to investigate--in his brand-new costume!
name: The Mist: Act Two of Four

description: Captain Fear's ship makes landfall in Manhattan. Jim Corrigan, who is aboard the ship, cannot remember who he is or what he is doing. He cannot even remember where he obtained the piece of the talisman that he is holding.
name: Merchants of Vengeance

description:
Superboy and Knockout are wanted by the law and go on the run. Things get worse when the daughter of one of Superman's most tenacious villains decides this is the perfect moment to strike.

While buying some new shades and perhaps jacket to replace those he lost in a fight last issue, Superboy hears about a pod of whales that washed ashore. He let's Knockout know, but she chases him away as he's praying to Darkseid, When Superboy leaves she finishes with "glory to Darkseid, i will use my strength in your name". Lifting up the whales, he receives a helping "hand" which he believes belongs to Knockout, but is in fact Supergirl's. Supergirl explains that she was looking for him when she stumbled upon the news of the whales and had come to help. Superboy says it's weird how "something so smart can get itself into so much trouble", which becomes a brilliant segue for Supergirl to bring up his situation, telling him he shouldn't run from the law and reminds him he's a member of the Superman family. Superboy still refuses to believe that Knockout is guilty. He also mentions how a) Superman was found guilty in the trial of Superman and later b) how Supergirl herself was involved with Lex Luthor. Knockout interrupts them and the 2 women break into a long fight, with Knockout seemingly having an advantage at first but neither of them completely beating the other. In the hospital, Rex asks Dubbilex if he could read Roxy's mind to see what he should buy her. Dubbilex is ammused by the sincerity and generosity of his request but says he has no psi powers any longer. Sparx drops into invite Superboy to the "event Horizon", a Rave (happening now) exclusive to super powered teens, that as Sparx says is "gonna change your life", providing the intro to Superboy and the Ravers. After Sparx splits Supergirl and Knockout from fighting, Supergirl tries to reason with Superboy again, where Superboy mentions Supergirl's past relationship with Luthor, and Supergirl ends up tearing his S symbol out (hence "Losin' It") Superboy is left sulking, he tells Sparx he wants to be alone but promises to attend the Event Horizon sometime later. Once again Knockout makes him fly her out saying there's nothing there he needs, except her, to which Superboy agrees although with some regret/despair. Later at night the police scout for evidence but Roxy Leech manages to hide the S shield.
name: Losin' It! Part 3 of 6: Ensnared!

description: 'Trial by Fire,' part 1 of 6. Beginning Mark Millar's climactic 6-part Swamp Thing storyline! A year has passed since the Swamp Thing was last seen, and the U.S. government sends Jason Woodrue, the man who discovered Swamp Thing's true nature, to navigate the now-unearthly landscape of the Louisiana bayou in search of the Earth Elemental. But Swamp Thing may be as altered as his environment...and John Constantine and the Phantom Stranger have their own plans for dealing with what he's become.
name: Trial by Fire, Part 1: Golden Days Before the End

description: Mink relives the night she died, Screech falls deeper into Dai Szae's seduction, and the Vamps learn of their bizarre connection to the vampire poet Dee.
name: Surfing the Red Wave

description: A lunch date with friends turns weird as Gateway City is suddenly menaced by the super-speeding mayhem of the Flash…but the face behind the scarlet mask is that of a man long thought dead! Also, the mysterious hero known as "Champion," who will have a profound effect on Dianas life, makes his debut!
name: Level 1

description:
The Hooded One brings news to the Lord of the Locusts that the armies of Pawa in the South have joined their cause, and the kingdom of Atheia has fallen to them. The Lord of the Locusts fears Thorn's power is awakening and their opportunity to seize control of her is slipping away, instructing The Hooded One to succeed soon or else kill her.

At Barrelhaven, Phoney Bone has the town in his thrall with his tales of dragons, and has stockpiled many of the townspeople's goods in payment for his “protection”. Late one night, Fone Bone finds a baby rat creature scrounging in the garbage. Staying at the inn that night, Thorn is once again visited by The Hooded One in her dreams, this time revealing its face like Gran'ma Ben's. She is only saved in the nick of time when Fone Bone wakes her to tell her about a Rat Creature cub that has found its way into the town. Thorn threatens to kill the cub so Fone Bone takes it back to the barn only to wait in agony for Thorn to kill it.
name: The Orphan

description:
In a cut-throat future where commerce is totally electronic and all information is in computer data form, big companies can corrupt control the people and work outside the law.  
 
Lady Supreme infiltrates the company of a woman named Coffin in Amber City and warns her to clean up her act. Coffin simply laughs at her as only moments before she had a staff member killed for making an investment that failed to make money, even thought it didn't loose money either. 
 
She laments that in her time in this new city she's failed to achieve much at all. She battled Loki with Supreme, who died during the battle, sending Loki back to the mists. 
 
When she comes across a robbery in an alleyway she extremely violently dispatches the robbers. Leaving her concerned that she is losing control. Lost in thought she runs into Glory who is concerned about her state of mind and her violent example to the citizens. Glory tells her that her mother would be ashamed.. which angers the test-tube born Supreme. Glory contradicts her saying that she is her mother.
name: Die & Let Die, Part 1 - World Without Pity

description: An encounter with the strange creature called The Maxx, who has made friends with Horridus, sends both he and The Maxx for a bizarre trip through the Dragon's subconscious, or, his "outback." They are retreived once Maxx's companion, Sarah, interrupts them. While the villainous Brainiape tries to rob a bank without the consent of the Vicious Circle, he is stopped by their agent, Powerhouse. Dragon and Rapture both suspect each other of infidelity.

In his office, Wynn plots against Sam and Twitch, setting up a secret meeting where they are to be eliminated. Meanwhile, Terry has finally linked Wynn to illegal activities, but blacks out due to a mysterious illness. In Rat City, Spawn builds a hideout. Cog wonders who is building it - Spawn or his costume.
name: The System
In Final Battle

description:
Hercules and Deathcry decide to take some personal time…on Earth’s moon! But will their trip go off without a hitch? Back at the mansion, Black Widow confronts Masque when she suspects the Avenger has ulterior motives. Plus, a dangerous intruder at Avengers Mansion!

Someone is attacking the Avengers from within the mansion....they all blame Madame Masque, but its not her!
name: Paranormal Activity

description:
In this issue.

Cap has been exiled from US soil under charges of treason. In a hotel, Sharon Carter gives Cap a new uniform but without the starts and stripes. She offers him guns but he does not accept them. Instead, she gives him a charged cool-temp plasma shield that attaches to his wrist and they leave London for Moldavia where Machinesmith has constructed a Argus Cannon to prod America towards war.

On the train to their destination they become under siege by Machinesmith's cyberops. They jump off the train and head to a US Air Force base nearest to Moldavia. They are followed into the base and Cap is forced to subdue his countrymen. Cap and Sharon steal an F-15 and flies into Moldavia air space, trying to become a target for the weapon. Cap locks on to the site of the weapon but not before the plane is destroyed by it.
name: Man Without A Country, Part 2: Plan A

description: Mysterious new client hires Foggy for real estate appraisal. Daredevil suspects a trap and investigates.
name: Smoky Mirrors

description: After being possessed by Emplate, Generation X try to save Synch.
name: Death in the Family

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Cover is an homage to the 1994 film Pulp Fiction. There is also a parody of the movie's famous dance scene.
name: Hulk Fiction

description: It's a remake of X-Men #6, with the Brotherhood trying to recruit Namor for their side.
name: Supreme Notions

description:
Summary

When Professor Xavier decides to not oppose the ascension of Avalon, Magneto is able to gain undeterred leadership of the colonized space station. Years later, with Colossus as his right-hand man, the divisions within mutantkind continue within Avalon as the society Magneto envisioned is threatened to forever be torn apart!

Synopsis

Colossus walks in on Magneto watching old news footage of Professor X announcing his support for Magneto to take willing mutants to be citizens of Avalon. When questioned why he was reviewing the past, Magneto laments that the prior events should only be experienced once. Colossus questions Magneto about the realities of his dream and Magneto solemnly declares that Avalon has become as violent as the human/mutant relations on Earth had become.

Outside of Magneto's quarters two factions of Acolytes are squabbling over the direction of mutantkind. Javitz and Senyaka battle Unuscione and Katu over the latter's views that Avalon should be moved to prevent further enculturation of humankind. Javitz and Senyaka, who are led by Fabian Cortez, believe that the opposing faction are isolationists and pushovers and that Earth is the mutant's birthright. Magneto interrupts the quarrel, but it is clear that Magneto holds no real authority over the unruly mutants.

Elsewhere, Rusty Collins and Sally Blevins (Skids) deliver a baby boy, the first child born on Avalon. Despite fears of rearing a child in the violent climate of Avalon, the arrival of X-Man Beast quelled their fears. During his examinations of the newborn, Beast discovers that their child has reached a new evolutionary landmark: he is a mutant capable of altering his own mutation at will, essentially capable of choosing his own powers. No longer homo superior but homo ultima, Beast fears for the child's future on Avalon.

Beast's fears are validated when Scanner reports to Fabian Cortez the news about the Collins/Blevins child. Hysteria erupts as Cortez's faction of Acolytes fear homo ultima will usurp mutantkind as the superior race and that homo ultima they will one day covet Earth as their own.

Elsewhere, Exodus' Acolytes similarly fear the repercussions the new child will bring to mutants. Exodus theorizes that when homo ultima rises, mutants will be the new "humans".

The two factions convene to seek counsel from Magneto. Knowing that his leadership has long been rejected, he leaves the dilemma for the citizens of Utopia to solve.

Fabian Cortez and Exodus create a truce to exterminate the child. Unuscione protests that he is just a child. Exodus interjects that Hitler was once a child. Unuscione turns silent and regretfully continues to follow Exodus' lead.

A battle ensues, but Skids, Rusty, and Beast prove to be adequate defenders of the young child. When their forces prove ineffective, Cortez orders Voght to asphyxiate the child using her mist powers. Voght does so and kills the child, apologizing in the shadows that she had done it in "self-defense", presumably to save her own life from Cortez's wrath.

With the child dead, Rusty's powers go out of control. Unuscione encases him in a force-field to prevent any harm from being done. The Acolytes stare the devastated young couple and offer for them to remain in Avalon. The refuse, protesting that they would rather live among the humans on Earth than remain in such savagery.

Cortez and Exodus make yet another truce, this time in an effort to work together against any future threat against mutantkind whether it be human or homo ultima. They declare a monitoring of all future births for this new race of mutants could someday prove to be more disastrous for mutants than humans ever were.

Elsewhere, Colossus announces to Magneto that he shall also depart from Avalon. Before he leaves, it is revealed that Magneto had magnetically manipulated the computers to reveal the Collins/Blevins child, a genetic human, to be something far more. Magneto knew the conflict would unite mutants, but was still mournful of the cost. Colossus questions what Magneto shall do when their fears become a reality and a new race does come to overtake the mutants. What will he do then when his fantasy becomes a reality?
name: What if Magneto Ruled All Mutants
Turning Point

description:
In the Arena diminutive Gax is pitted against a massive crusher robot and Spuckler takes on the many toothed Jaggasaur. Thankfully the Jaggasaur is too much of a show-off in battle and inadvertently aids the crew in their escape. 
                                    
Akiko finds she has something of a connection with the usually incomprehensible Poog which leads her to a revelation that just might save them all.

name: Fire From Heaven, Part. 9

description: When things fall apart in the world of Grendel, they fall fast -- and hard! Albert's vigilante acts against the Grendels have caused their order to unravel; as chief of the Grendels, Hack must stop Albert or lose control of the clan -- a decision complicated by the fact that Hack is in love with Albert's mother, Dana; and Dana's relationship with Albert is about to fall apart because of her affection for Hack. Which is more important to Hack -- his status or his love for Dana? And which is more important to Dana -- her son or her lover? In the Indianapolis of the future, as they gear up for one bad-ass rally royale, it's one helluva time to fall in love.
name: Book 6

volume.name: Grendel Tales: The Devil May Care

name: Fall of the Tempo, Part Two of Two

description: Wolverine continues to regress into an animal at the hands of Genesis. Professor Xavier uses his abilities in an ethically-unsound manner. Plus, the first appearance of Ozymandias, immortal servant to Apocalypse!
name: The Road to Casablanca

story_arc_credits.name: The Helix of an Age Foretold

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Helix of an Age Foretold

description:
Wolverine verges on the brink of insanity when his animal instincts take over. Wolverine and the X-Men continue to fight the stone creatures that Ozymandias has created. Will Logan find enough control to get his teammates out of harm’s way?

Story continued from Uncanny X-Men #332.
name: The Helix of an Age Foretold

story_arc_credits.name: The Helix of an Age Foretold

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Helix of an Age Foretold

description:
Continued from X-Man #14. Cable and Nate Grey push each other to the limit. Blaquesmith wants Cable to eliminate the "anomaly," but Cable wants to help the boy. It isn't until Nate exceeds what his body can hold that the fight ends and Cable is given the choice to kill Nate or help him restore his body. Cable chooses the latter. Blaquesmith reveals in this issue the role he plays as Cable's executioner if things ever get out of hand.
 
Note: This issue contains part two of a brief history of Cable.

Error: The scene with Psylocke references Uncanny X-Men #331 as the issue in which she is injured by Sabretooth. It actually occurred in #328.
name: There is a Reaction!

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Luse and Cassy are strolling through the streets as Luse hears that familiar cry...NYAR! The Purple Marauder has returned and Luse begs Cassy to help kill him. Will Luse live the dream? Wait...crap Luse gets captured by someone.
name: Six: Night of the Marauder

description: This issue picks up with Catwoman stealing a microchip for a client. During the course of which Hellhound and a squad of ninjas show up capturing Catwoman imprisoning her on a ship.
name: Devil Does Your Dog Bite

description: Batman fought Ultimate Clayface; Ventriloquist attacked along with Amygdala and Rhino. Batman felt he was dreaming, but was unable to wake himself. Tally Man came next. Corrosive Man, Mahakala, and others followed. Batman woke up. Narcosis - a new villain - was standing above him. He sprayed Batman with more dream gas and left.
name: 50th Issue Villain Special

description: This wiki page is a stub. Hit the edit button above to add to this article.
name: Life Preservation

description:
The Legion's ultimate battle with the Fatal Five escalates when the team discovers that the United Planets has been corrupted--turning the entire galaxy against the Legionnaires.

As the Legion continues against the Fatal Five and an assassination attempt, President Chu reveals herself as the mastermind behind the attack and several other negative incidents of the United Planets. Unfortunately for Chu, Cosmic Boy and the Legion Espionage Squad had been in the know and set up a sting. With Chu behind bars, Legion founder RJ Brande is elected the new president of the United Planets and the Legion draft is abolished. The Legion is now free to choose their own members.
name: Trust

description: Turok continues to flashback to the time when he sought to win the hand in marriage of Ravenwing, the chief's daughter, by bringing back a great offering.
name: Son Of Stone - Part 2

description: Spawn and Terry both battle their personal demons. Spawn's suit has completely taken control of him. He hemorrhages and sprouts growth until he is helped by Cog. Terry blacks out and is struck by a semi-. The accident lands him in the hospital. Cy-Gor is in New York city looking for Spawn.
name: Helter Skelter

description: Last month, a group of clones volunteered to be transformed by the Paracelsus Matrix, the genetic retrovirus everyone's after. This month, witness the results: a whole new squad of Heartbreakers based on Queenie's DNA and the memories of her original Club Squad! While Tex is busy training these "newborn" soldiers, Queenie heads off to negotiate an arms deal -- but unbeknownst to her, she's also headed for a final showdown with Biovoc agent Rusk!
Cain murders Abel once too often. So Goldie the infant Gargoyle runs away from the House of Secrets, only to fall under the seductive influence of a limbless being calling himself Tempto.
name: The Goldie Factor, Part One

description:
Drawn once more into the sinister dealings of his former comrade The Fact, Flex encounters a mysterious rock star whose connection to the Hero of the Beach may hold the key to saving them both.

It all starts when Flex Mentallo, a man capable of altering reality flexing its WONDERFUL! muscles, preventing a bomb detonates in a fast food restaurant. Further research will lead to the conclusion that The Fact, his old wanderings, is somehow involved in the matter, and that the same reality, which is entering in apparent conflict with other realities as the entropy increases-is threatened. And that also includes that the reader's world.
name: "After the Fact", Part One: Flowery Atomic Heart

description:
A Rage is Arkham Part 2 After last issue's finale, Tommy has to think quickly to escape arrest. Meanwhile the Mawzir begins to track Tommy for recruitment as an agent of the Lords of the Gun. With word out that Tommy has accepted the hit on the Joker, Tommy picks up a list of additional Arkham inmates with hits on their head. Even with Batman watching, Tommy manages to make his way into Arkham, but everything does not turn out as planned.

Tommy has had near-free run of Arkham Asylum, shooting dead many horrible people in order to fill many contracts. But his attempt to do the world a favor by plugging the Joker goes horribly, horribly wrong.
name: A Rage in Arkham, Part Two

description:
In "Truth and Justice," Superman, now out of retirement, inspires fellow super-heroes Green Lantern, Hawkman, and others to appear before the public and announce their return from self-imposed exile. Batman, Green Arrow, and others refuse to join Superman and form an allegiance with Lex Luthor.

This issue is also the first appearance of Red Robin.
name: Truth And Justice

description: While in the Lost Land to teach Andy hunting and survival tactics, Turok comes across some old friends and old enemies.
name: Bred Up In Darkness - Part 1

description:
Overview
They say crises, like tragedies, come in threes, and Concrete has had his share since he's come into contact with the people of Earth First!. Now comes a fourth: a crisis of conscience. Faced with the overwhelming evidence of humankind's wounding of Mother Earth, can Concrete continue to merely observe and chronicle the group's activities? Or will he abandon his passivity and embrace his new friends' militant agenda?

Joshua's dad loves him -- Josh knows that 'cause his dad beats him. That's how dads show affection. And that's how Joshua will show his new friend that he loves him, when his friend finally hatches from his "Egg." Frank Lovece and Christopher Schenck spin a web of an abusive father and a mysterious egg in this new, four-part serial. Also, Paul Pope, Renée French, and Shannon Wheeler provide new installments of "The One Trick Rip-Off," "The Ninth Gland," and "Too Much Coffee Man," all under a haunting painting by August Hall, whose work has graced Vertigo's The Books of Magic.

OverviewThe world's greatest paranormal detective meets the world's greatest paranormal! Something happened a long time ago, something sorcerous and secret, something involving murder. This "something" has swallowed up Hellboy and Ghost -- an evil so deep they've fallen off the face of the earth. And when they land, there will be hell to pay.

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: Hartigan's free. Nancy's in trouble. And somewhere there's a guy who's got them both on the run. A little man. A predator of innocence. A yellow bastard.

person_credits.name: Frank Miller
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: Those who travel the haunted paths of The Tangled Skein are warned to make an offering of protection to the demons that rule the woods. When a traveling party fails to make that sacrifice, they pay the price in another way -- the young woman traveling with them is overcome with great illness. Now it's up to Usagi to exorcise the demons the only way he knows how -- in battle.
name: The Wrath of the Tangled Skein

person_credits.name: Stan Sakai
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Believing that Artemis is being tortured, Diana ventures in to Hell to rescue her only to find that Artemis is very much alive and well. Unable to leave Artemis behind and unwilling to turn a blind eye to the suffering of even the coldest demon, Diana finds herself in trouble when she intervenes in one demon's torture. Will Artemis sacrifice all that she's gained to save Diana and reclaim her old life?
name: Into the Pit

description: Dr. Orchid's brother, a cult leader, plotted to destroy his twin. Azrael single-handedly fought the cult away when it attacked. Orchid planned to use Azrael for his own benefit.
name: Angel in Flames part two: The Enemy Around Us

description: Batman and Deadman join forces in the Peruvian jungle
name: The Deadman Connection part 2

description: Fed up with his host, Scarface vows to kill a member of the Ventriloquist's family, putting Batman in the strange position of trying to protect the Ventriloquist from himself.
name: His Master's Voice

description:
Batman investigates the murder of an unidentified woman.

Harvey Dent is cured of his Two-Face persona, but with him dating a pair of twins, how long can it last?

Batman is an "Equal Rights Justice Dispenser!" Or is it all a dream?

A serial killer is going around Gotham killing people over the minor annoyances of everyday life.

Les Farrel would KILL to be able to play the trumpet like Coley Treadwell...

Notes:

  • Ranked #62 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".

concept_credits.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

first_appearance_concepts.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

description: "Infected" part 1! The Dark Knight faces a horrific new foe with a preference for organic weaponry--specifically, bullets made from bone. But as Batman pursues this mysterious killer, the trail leads to a terrible source: the US government.
name: Infected Part 1 of 2

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
Tim, having determined to stay away from his family and friends so they are no longer in danger, goes to Brighton Beach, where he used to vacation. He carries the miniature statue of his friend Jimmy, who was turned into that state by Reverend Slaggingham in issue 9.

Tim remembers when he and Jimmy were at the beach as kids. His dad tells them a story about how all the pier workers are really cannibal pirates in disguise, which they almost believe until his aunt tells him it's not.

Tim misses being a carefree kid, his life now having been changed by both his mother's death and the world of magic.

In the flashback, kid-Tim pulls an ankh out of a pincer-toy machine. They meet a strange old fisher man, J. Alfred Skinner, who says he'll trade them an all-day pass to the rides on the pier for the ankh. He wants to use it as a lure on his fishing rod, to catch a muddle-mullah, a strange creature of the deep.

The kids think he's one of the pirates, but they give him the ankh and take the passes.

In the present, Tim laments that his new tattoos won't let him use his own magic to fix Jimmy. He considers asking John Constantine to do it, and maybe he'll be able to stay with him, too. Unseen by Tim, Skinner is watching him.

In the past, Tim and Jimmy are on the Ferris Wheel when it gets stuck in place. They're worried, but also enjoy just imagining about other lands while they're stuck.

Tim, wandering around feeling sorry for himself, sees Death (wearing the ankh) and Skinner. Skinner's seemingly dead body still stands by the side of the pier, fishing for the muddle-mullah, while his spirit talks with Death about his fishing attempts. The muddle-mullah took part of his finger, and his soul, as a child.

Death volunteers Tim to help with Skinner's problem. She also asks for Jimmy, who is dead, not just transformed. Tim gives up Jimmy and goes to find the muddle-mullah, who turns out to be a normal crab. He gives it to Skinner.

Death asks Tim if he wants to go get some pancakes.
name: Used To Bes

description: Foxglove and her friends enter Death's realm, where Hazel learns the secret of her young son Alvie. Who will live and who will die is decided, and Death herself reveals the significance of The Time of Your Life.
name: Chapter Three: The Time of Your Life

volume.name: Death: The Time of Your Life

description: "Race Against Time - Chapter Two: Sibling Rivalry." While pinballing through the timestream, Wally West runs into Don and Dawn Allen (Barry Allen's kids) in the 30th century. Meanwhile, the new Polaris announces his presence, and Linda Park continues hanging out with the blue-clad Flash from the future while worrying about Wally.
name: Race Against Time! Part 2: Sibling Rivalry

description:
The mysterious enemy hunting the Darkstars stands revealed. Can Green Lantern and the greatest hero of Planet Rann, Adam Strange, help the interstellar police force in their darkest hour, or is this the end of the Darkstars forever?

Kyle and Donna get into it for a bit as they are still awkward around each other after their fight a few issues back. After she explains to Kyle the situation he offers to help. Back on Rann they prepare for the inevitable confrontation and Adam strange comes to assist them.

Back on the ship Kyle’s fills Donna in on what he was up to in her absence when they get attacked. They defend themselves.

On Rann a Darkstar is killed as the invader and his troop’s teleport right in and start to take down the Darkstars. He is revealed as lord Grayven and singlehandedly takes out john and Adam. Kyle and Donna finish off their assailants and rush to the planet they find the darkstars defeated and Grayven turns his attention and power to them.
name: Who Will Die?

description: "Difficult Beginnings" part 1! When John Constantine banished his dark side to hell he never expected he would miss it. Spiritually adrift, Constantine heads off to nowhere in particular, and finds himself at the door of the place he least wants to be.
name: Difficult Beginnings, Part One: The Single-Sided Coin

description: The Trickster comes to Manchester to perpetrate the scam of the decade, the sting to end all stings. He counted on Impulse showing up...but not White Lightning!
name: Faith

description: Newly empowered as Jack Frost, Dane faces his first great challenge as an Invisible when he returns to Liverpool to see his mother, but runs into an ambush.
name: Liverpool
Purge, Part 1: Now It's Time

description:
Jesus de Sade wants his secret stash. Starr wants some relief. And Jesse Custer and Cassidy want some answers. Plus, the secret of the Grail is revealed!

Jesse and Cassidy discover the cause of Cass' girlfriend's death; Starr explains his conspiracy and gets a surprise; De Sade plans his party.
name: Boys Will Be Boys (Hunters Part 2)

description: Robin called Oracle, who attempted to pinpoint his location. Ariana went out with friends, and one of the boys tried to take advantage of her. She was able to get away from him before anything happened. The police arrived and took down Zeus' gang. Tim picked up Ariana the next morning - she'd dyed her hair back to normal.
name: Iliads and Oddities

description: The Golden Age Sandman teams up with Ted Knight--the original Starman and future JSAer--to discover the secret behind the city's recent slew of accidents and deaths!
name: The Mist: Act Three of Four
A Moving Prayer (The Pilgrimage Of Lucas Hart Epilogue)

description: The Spectre goes into action when a building is haunted by the spirits of dead slaves. Agent Shadrach targets a family in the building who holds a fragment of the powerful American Talisman.
name: The Poisoned Land

description:
Jack Knight is once again reunited with his brother David, his immediate--and slain--predecessor as Starman, in this standalone issue. And even though the reunion is bittersweet between the siblings, it's the appearance of another family member that brings Jack to tears.

Talking With David, '96, has Jack and David Knight playing pirate with a surprise waiting for Jack in port.
name: Talking With David, '96

description: Supergirl arrives in Hawaii to knock some sense into the Teen of Steel. However, she'll have to get past the powerhouse bombshell known as Knockout first.
name: Losin' It! Part 4 of 6: Tough Love

description: 'Trial by Fire,' part 2 of 6. Mark Millar's climactic Swamp Thing storyline continues: As Jason Woodrue seeks help in stopping Swamp Thing's plans to destroy humankind, Timothy Raven prepares to invoke the spirit of Anton Arcane; Lady Jane and the Parliament of Trees face possibly their last stand against The Word; and Abby and Chester make desperate plans of their own.
name: Trial by Fire, Part 2: The Word of God

description: If last issues reappearance of the late Barry Allen Flash wasn't enough of a mystery, Diana is attacked by another dead man…the evil Green Lantern, Sinestro! Also, Champion makes his heroic debut.
name: Level 2

description:
Lucius Down, who has been out searching for Gran'ma Ben for two days, returns to find the town barricaded. He protests about Phoney appointing himself leader, and orders the fences to be torn down, but the townsfolk, terrified of dragons, turn against him and refuse to even let him back into his own tavern.

In the barn, Smiley is delighted to meet the Rat Creature cub, and promptly adopts him as a pet. Fone Bone meets with Lucius and explains what happened in the forest. Lucius fears that the Rat Creatures evacuating the valley could be a precursor to another sneak attack like the Nights of Lightning.

Meanwhile, the Hooded One addresses his army of Rat Creatures and men from Pawa. He tells them the two laws that the Lord of the Locusts has set down for them and then orders them to prepare for war.
name: War

description: Terry learns that he will die in two months from a malignant brain tumor. Spawn is torn apart by the belief that Terry's a traitor, but he uses all his power to heal him. This sends Spawn hurtling to Hell's second level, where he is immediately attacked by creatures trying to drain his life-sustaining necroplasm. Then suddenly, memories of past injustices provoke Al into a rage and he rises to fight again.
name: Choices

description: Hawkeye and Masque take down the intruder who managed to infiltrate Avengers Mansion. When the identity of the interloper is revealed, Black Widow discovers he’s a dangerous acquaintance! Who is Benedict? And why has he kidnapped Masque?
name: Trust

description:
In this issue.

Cap and Sharon's F-15 was just blown out of the sky by the Argus Canon. Cap's parachute opened, Sharon's didn't. So what does our boy do? He ditches his and saves her.

They then commandeer a Moldovan Army vehicle, and barge into the Military base where the Argus canon is being held. They are promptly captured by the Machinesmith. He tells them how He was inside Cap's brain while he was frozen, and he now knows EVERYTHING that Cap knows. Including SHIELD Helicarrier override codes, which he uses to direct the Helicarrier toward Mt. Hood. Machinesmith then Teleports to Camp David to assasinate the President of the United States, and leaves Cap to figure out how to save the Helicarrier, and the President all from Moldovia.
name: Man without a Country, Part 3: Plan B
The Devil's Work!

description:
Generation X battels the evil crazed Synch and frees him of Emplate.

X-Cutioner is out for Skin's blood!
name: Out of Sync!

description: Doc Samson and She-Hulk vs Molecule Man! Meanwhile, Matt Talbot finds out that his previous actions may have repercussions. And the citizens of Freehold decide on Omnibus's punishment. Also, where has Leader been hiding all this while?
name: Private Sessions
Call Her...Commanda!

description: A post-hypnotic command by The Jackal has control over Spider-Man -- and demands he kill Mary Jane!  The Scarlet Spider arrives to save her and quickly realizes he as no choice but to kill Spider-Man.  A power plant becomes the final resting place for the web-slinger as he becomes trapped under a generator, which soon explodes.  The Scarlet Spider is thrown out of the building by the explosion and, when rescued, is mistaken for Peter Parker.  He must now live a lie.
name: What if Scarlet Spider killed Spider-Man?
Survivors of the Storm

description: Rogue fights an unknown assailant!
name: Adrift

description:
Flying the Sky boat to find  Alia Rellapor Akiko dreams what might be ahead for them as they go to the rescue of the young Prince. 
 
The crew face a longer journey without their books and maps and things get worse when they sail into a skugbit storm and once again fine themselves in the ocean.
Hercules saves people. Bet you didn't see that one coming.
name: The Trial of Hercules: Part 1
